An unknown number of residents attacked the man in the early hours of this morning, burning him to death. JOHANNESBURG Police are investigating a case of murder after a man was allegedly necklaced by residents in the Zandspruit informal settlement, north of Johannesburg. It is understood that an unknown number of residents attacked the man in the early hours of this morning.He is believed to be involved in a string of robberies and other crimes in the community.The police's Balan Muthan says: It is alleged by members of the community that this individual was involved in housebreaking and house robbery. To confirm exactly what led to this incident [the] investigation needs to be complete. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)